{
  "page": "Johanna Swann",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\"><img alt=\"House Swann.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/50px-House_Swann.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/75px-House_Swann.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/100px-House_Swann.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Johanna Swann<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Black Swan</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\"><img alt=\"House Swann.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/50px-House_Swann.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/75px-House_Swann.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/100px-House_Swann.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Lady_Johanna,_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Lady Johanna, the Black Swan by viscardiac.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5b/Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png/350px-Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"467\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5b/Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png/525px-Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5b/Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png/700px-Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png 2x\" /></a><div>Johanna Swann, by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://viscardiac.tumblr.com/\">viscardiac</a> ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe Black Swan<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\">House Swann</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Marcher</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_81_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">81</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_94_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">94&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rogue_Prince\" title=\"The Rogue Prince\">The Rogue Prince</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Johanna Swann</b>, known as <b>the Black Swan</b>, was a noblewoman from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\">House Swann</a> during the reign of kings <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>. She became an influential <a href=\"/index.php/Courtesan\" title=\"Courtesan\">courtesan</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Johanna_Swann&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After driving <a href=\"/index.php/Pirates\" title=\"Pirates\">pirates</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_96_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">96&#160;AC</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a> gradually became greedier with their tolls for passage. Along with <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">money</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lysene</a> captains also began taking women, girls, and boys to turn into <a href=\"/index.php/Slavery\" title=\"Slavery\">slaves</a> for their <a href=\"/index.php/Pillow_house\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pillow house\">pillow houses</a>. Johanna was enslaved when she was fifteen, but her stingy uncle, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\">Swann</a>, refused to ransom her. After being sold to a pillow house, Johanna became a celebrated <a href=\"/index.php/Courtesan\" title=\"Courtesan\">courtesan</a> known as the Black Swan, the eventual ruler of Lys in all but name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/131_AC\" title=\"131 AC\">131&#160;AC</a> the Lysene admiral <a href=\"/index.php/Sharako_Lohar\" title=\"Sharako Lohar\">Sharako Lohar</a> was slain by a rival in competition for Johanna's affections. Since he had been blamed by <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myrmen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyroshi</a> for the disastrous <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Gullet\" title=\"Battle of the Gullet\">Battle of the Gullet</a> in the previous year, Sharako's death was initially viewed by Lyseni as a political murder orchestrated by the Myrish. The <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a> collapsed into the <a href=\"/index.php/Daughters%27_War\" title=\"Daughters&#39; War\">Daughters' War</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Johanna's fate is unknown.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Johanna_Swann&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Heirs of the Dragon - A Question of Succession.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued)#Johanna_Swann\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued)\">Johanna Swann</a> calculation.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - The Hooded Hand.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404040340\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.096 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.318 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 697/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10589/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 8745/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1769/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1978/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.200/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.57 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  298.228      1 -total\n 95.17%  283.838      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 94.69%  282.405      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.31%   33.723     12 Te